annotationA: Uncharacterized protein, isoform A; ATP binding; ATP-dependent RNA helicase activity; nucleic acid binding; helicase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: mRNA splicing, via spliceosome
annotationB: 60S ribosomal protein L11; Component of the ribosome, a large ribonucleoprotein complex responsible for the synthesis of proteins in the cell. The small ribosomal subunit (SSU) binds messenger RNAs (mRNAs) and translates the encoded message by selecting cognate aminoacyl- transfer RNA (tRNA) molecules. The large subunit (LSU) contains the ribosomal catalytic site termed the peptidyl transferase center (PTC), which catalyzes the formation of peptide bonds, thereby polymerizing the amino acids delivered by tRNAs into a polypeptide chain.
